<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="749" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/10–1848: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-19T18:00:00-05:00">October 19, 1948—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1469. Dept opinion proposed text warning (your 1926, Oct. 18)
                            unnecessarily explicit and may have unduly damaging effect Nationalist
                            position north China. Fol[lowing] substitute phraseology recommended:
                                <pb facs="0864" n="854" xml:id="pg_854"/>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Military situation north China appears to indicate that
                                    hostilities may spread to areas hitherto peaceful and that
                                    normal transportation facilities may be completely disrupted.
                                    Accordingly American citizens should consider desirability
                                    evacuation at this time while normal transportation facilities
                                    are still available.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>